@robjohnston1433well, here’s the milk-toast comment for the day… 

There are too many glaring issues to list with the way they are handling this series, and we’re only 2 episodes in. Feeling quite skeptical about what could be done to salvage this trope filled kindergarten romp. Being British and speaking like a Californian pre-teen is not exactly a high bar for acting ability, to be fair though, the writers really did them dirty. 

This is the kind of generic Alien content that actually makes me pine for Prometheus… wish we had seen that whole vision played out without all the “Aliens” fanboy rage taking influence.

@bdp2868 Everything has already been said before cinema was even born. Even Star Wars basically followed a story and structure laid out before our current civilization was born, the hero's journey. Just like dancing only has 3 moves, sideways/front & back/up, there are not that many stories you can tell that haven't been told a million times before. The only thing new is what new twist can you put on it. 

As for different takes offending people, like who? The professional outrage class? In the grand scheme of things they may be loud, but they offer no purchasing power that makes it worth their while listening to them. And as American Eagle is now proving, once you ignore them they have no power. 

As for liking this show, that is okay. Slop seems to be very popular right now. You're in good company.

